# Copy to `.env.standalone` in the repo root (gitignored).
# Simple start/stop/restart for events: see scripts/PHOTO-BOOTH-END-USER-START.txt
# Loaded automatically by `scripts/run-api-standalone.sh` and `scripts/run-api-standalone.bat`.
# One command starts API + print watcher together (scripts/photo_booth_standalone.py).
# When the server starts, the console prints how to test from your phone: open http://<LAN>:<PORT>/health
# in the phone browser (expect JSON "status":"ok"). Windows step-by-step: scripts/README-WINDOWS-STANDALONE.txt

# --- API (optional overrides; same as shell env) ---
# API_PORT=8001
# Windows: if bind fails with WinError 10013 (Hyper-V/WSL port exclusion), try: API_PORT=18080
# PHOTOBOOTH_STRICT_PORT=1   # fail if API_PORT busy (default: auto-pick 8002, 8003, …)
#
# --- Same URL for your mobile APK after stop/restart (recommended) ---
# • Stop / restart / Ctrl+C does NOT change this computer's Wi-Fi IP — you do NOT rebuild the app for that.
# • What CAN change is the PORT if 8001 is busy and the server picks 8002+ instead.
# • To always use the same http://<THIS-PC-IP>:PORT as in PHOTOBOOTH_API_BASE, pin the port:
#     API_PORT=8001
#     PHOTOBOOTH_STRICT_PORT=1
#   If start fails "port busy", run scripts\stop-photo-booth-standalone.bat (Windows) or
#   ./scripts/stop-photo-booth-standalone.sh, then start again — IP is still the same.
# DATA_DIR=./data-standalone
# FRAMES_DIR=./shared/frames

# --- Printer (auto-starts print watcher when set) ---
# Exact queue name: Windows → Settings → Printers; Mac/Linux → lpstat -p
PHOTOBOOTH_PRINTER_NAME="EPSON L3250 Series"

# Only if you want to turn printing OFF while keeping the name above:
# PHOTOBOOTH_ENABLE_PRINT_WATCHER=0

# Watch mode: finals (default) = any **/finals/** under DATA_DIR; queue = print-queue → print → print-archive
# PHOTOBOOTH_PRINT_WATCH_MODE=queue

# Optional: directory the watcher uses (defaults to DATA_DIR)
# PHOTOBOOTH_DATA_DIR=

# Queue mode paths (optional; default under DATA_DIR)
# PHOTOBOOTH_PRINT_QUEUE_DIR=
# PHOTOBOOTH_PRINT_ARCHIVE_DIR=

# API: after /compose/final, also copy a unique file into print-queue (use with PHOTOBOOTH_PRINT_WATCH_MODE=queue)
# PHOTOBOOTH_COPY_FINAL_TO_PRINT_QUEUE=1
